      passage: `Whereas researchers long thought the Congo rainforest constrained the initial expansion of Bantu-speaking peoples (which today include the Kuria in Tanzania and the Shona in Zimbabwe) across subequatorial Africa, recent studies indicate that early Bantu communities managed to ______ the rainforest, a feat facilitated by drier conditions that opened up viable corridors through the vegetation.`,
